@node deficons
These icons are supposed to be used with progs such as DefIcons or DOpus5.5+, or any prog that lets you define an icon for a type of file.
I've tried to provide the main kinds of files, like picture, sound, etc...

To use them, just copy them to Envarc:sys and Env:sys, then configure your filetype util. Be sure to change the icon type for def_#?disk.info to "disk". In the drawer, they're project icon so that they can be displayed.

These icons are recolored versions of icons made by Roman Patzner, Trevor Morris and Mattias Eriksson. The original idea of deficons drawn like this is from R. Patzner.
@endnode

@node tmb
These brushes are meant to be used with Toolmanager or equivalent progs.

The simplier way to use them is to copy them to MagicWB: (providing you installed those which came with MagicWB2.0). I've renamed them so that they are the same ones that the originals, just a little bit more colorful :)

The brushes were originally drawn by R.E. Spence for his Fantastic WB archives, except Shapeshifter.brush which was originally drawn by R. Patzner. Some others brushes were created by me, using other brushes/icons from other collections.
@endnode

